repository.corpname: Digital Collections and Archives, Tufts University

did.abstract: This collection contains photographic prints, negatives, and CDs of digital photographs taken by JD Sloan, documenting university events and campus life between approximately 1978 and 2013.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Gift of J. D. Sloan, and transferred by the Office of the Board of Trustees, 2018, accession MS-2019-004.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged in two chronological series by format: Photographic prints and negatives; and Born digital materials.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: J. D. Sloan is an American photographer born in 1946 in Springfield, Massachusetts. From the late 1970s through the mid 2010s, Sloan took photographs documenting university events and campus life at Tufts University.

Sloan's work is held in the collections of the Reva and David Logan Foundation in Chicago, IL; the Carnegie Museum of Art in Pittsburgh, PA; and the Harry Ransom Center in Austin, TX, among others. He is the owner of JD Sloan Photographs.

custodhist.head: Custodial History
custodhist.p: This collection was sent to the Office of the Board of Trustees in the fall of 2017, and was transferred to DCA in July of 2018.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: J. D. Sloan Photographs, 1978-2013. Tufts University. Digital Collections and Archives. Medford, MA.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: This collection was processed by Leah Edelman in 2018. Materials were placed in archival boxes if the original housing was damaged, and loose materials were placed in folders where needed. Received rough chronological order was maintained. Data from initial cataloging provided by the Office of the Board of the Trustees was repurposed to create detailed file level records for photographic prints, negatives, and CDs. Series level descriptions as well as a finding aid were also created at the time of processing.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains photographic prints, negatives, and CDs of digital photographs taken by JD Sloan, documenting university events and campus life between approximately 1978 and 2013. Highlights include speakers and distinguished guests visiting Tufts, annual events such as Commencement and reunions, openings of buildings and facilities on all campuses, portraits of Tufts staff and presidents, and images of day to day campus life.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material in this collection may be protected by copyright and other rights. Please see "Reproduction and Use" on the Digital Collections and Archives website for more information about reproductions and permission to publish. Any intellectual property rights that the donor possesses have been transferred to Tufts University.

arrangement.p: This series is arranged roughly chronologically.
